3. `get(key)` - This fetches the value associated with the given `key` from Redis. If the key doesn't exist, it returns `null`.

4. `set(key, value, duration)` - This sets the value of the given `key` in Redis with an expiry time of `duration` seconds. It returns a promise that resolves to `true`.

5. `del(key)` - This deletes the given `key` and its corresponding value from Redis. It returns a promise that resolves to `true`.

